wikipedia_page.main: William Henry Bather (12 December 1861 – 3 January 1939) was an English cricketer. He played six first-class matches for Cambridge University Cricket Club between 1882 and 1883. He also played cricket at county level for Hertfordshire and, between 1879 and 1892, for Shropshire.He was educated at Rossall School and Cambridge University. He later became a Church of England clergyman.

response: *William Bather (1861-1939) born at Meole Brace, first-class cricketer, later clergyman.
